好吧，我在那里见

513
00:39:14,520 --> 00:39:17,320
Nobody put chains on anything.
没人用铁链锁门

514
00:39:17,400 --> 00:39:20,120
Who told you they put chains on the windows and doors?
谁告诉你有人用铁链锁住了门窗？

515
00:39:20,200 --> 00:39:21,960
It was all ablaze when we arrived.
我们到的时候全是大火

516
00:39:22,040 --> 00:39:24,600
Ufuk was crying out, trying to get inside.
乌福克哭了，想进去救人

517
00:39:24,680 --> 00:39:27,120
We did our best, but it was impossible.
我们已经尽力了，但那是不可能的

518
00:39:27,680 --> 00:39:32,760
We were torn between holding Ufuk back and trying to put out the fire.
我们在阻止乌福克和试图扑灭大火之间左右为难。

519
00:39:34,160 --> 00:39:38,040
That's when something fell on Ufuk's head. A beam or something.
就在那时  一根横梁掉下来砸中乌福克的头

520
00:39:38,120 --> 00:39:39,640
He was already a half-wit.
他本来就是个笨蛋

521
00:39:40,320 --> 00:39:42,200
After that, he became really strange.
在那之后，他变得很奇怪

522
00:39:43,600 --> 00:39:45,000
What were you doing there?
你当时在哪里干什么？

523
00:39:45,480 --> 00:39:49,360
Ufuk had been talking about it a while.
乌福克一直在说那些话

524
00:39:49,920 --> 00:39:52,800
Saying he'd burn that place down, saying he'd kill Tayyar.
说是他烧掉了房子  是他杀掉了塔亚尔一家

525
00:39:53,520 --> 00:39:56,600
When we saw Ufuk running to the house, we followed him.
当我们看到乌福克奔向房屋时，我们紧跟着他

526
00:39:57,120 --> 00:40:00,200
To stop him from doing something stupid. But we couldn't.
阻止他做一些愚蠢的事情，但是我们不能

527
00:40:00,280 --> 00:40:04,800
Why did Ufuk want to kill Tayyar?
乌福克为什么要杀死塔亚尔一家？

528
00:40:04,880 --> 00:40:07,920
Because he was a thief, or because he was Romani? Why?
是因为他是小偷，还是因为他是吉普赛人？为什么？

529
00:40:08,000 --> 00:40:11,960
He's mad, I'm telling you. You can't ask a madman why he did what.
他疯了，我告诉你  你不能问一个疯子做事的原因

530
00:40:12,040 --> 00:40:15,160
Tayyar might've given him dirty looks, for all I know.
就我所知，塔亚可能没给他好脸色

531
00:40:15,240 --> 00:40:17,400
It's a small place.
这是个小地方

532
00:40:18,200 --> 00:40:20,120
There's nothing to do but bicker.
除了争吵外别无他法

533
00:40:22,680 --> 00:40:26,680
You think being involved with my daughter makes you immortal?
你以为和我女儿在一起就能不死了吗？

534
00:40:29,120 --> 00:40:30,520
Alright.
好的

535
00:40:32,200 --> 00:40:36,120
If you're not going to bleed for now,
如果你暂时不死

536
00:40:37,360 --> 00:40:39,720
whom would you like to take your place?
谁来代替你？

537
00:40:41,840 --> 00:40:44,240
How about your blood brother?
你该死的兄弟怎么样？

538
00:40:46,320 --> 00:40:48,960
That works, right? That works beautifully.
那行得通，对吗？那行得通

539
00:40:50,080 --> 00:40:52,480
I think that would be so poetic.
我认为那太诗意了

540
00:40:59,840 --> 00:41:00,840
Hello.
你好

541
00:41:01,640 --> 00:41:03,720
Who are you looking for.
你在找谁

542
00:41:03,800 --> 00:41:06,400
- We're looking for Anchor Rü?tü. - I don't know him.
-我们在找吕泰-我不认识他

543
00:41:07,040 --> 00:41:09,680
They told us everyone in Kumkap? would know him.
有人告诉我们在库姆卡皮的每个人都认识他

544
00:41:09,760 --> 00:41:12,200
Especially you.
尤其是你

545
00:41:12,800 --> 00:41:14,280
There must've been a mistake.
肯定是误会

546
00:41:22,480 --> 00:41:25,640
I don't know anything. I don't know any Rü?tü.
我什么都不知道  我不认识这个人

547
00:41:25,720 --> 00:41:29,440
We aren't after you. Just tell me where Anchor Rü?tü is.
我们不是冲你来的，只需告诉我吕泰在哪里

548
00:41:31,640 --> 00:41:34,160
- There's this street. - Where is it?
-这条街-在哪里？

549
00:41:38,840 --> 00:41:40,040
You have a deal.
成交

550
00:41:42,200 --> 00:41:43,480
Anchor Rü?tü?
吕泰？

551
00:41:45,920 --> 00:41:47,440
Yes? What do you want?
是的  你想要什么

552
00:41:50,360 --> 00:41:52,600
I want this man. His name is Hamza Kaymak.
我需要一个名叫哈姆萨·凯马克的人

553
00:41:53,240 --> 00:41:55,000
What does it have to do with me?
这跟我有什么关系

554
00:41:55,560 --> 00:41:57,800
He paid a smuggler to take him across the border.
他付钱给走私犯带他过境

555
00:41:58,400 --> 00:42:00,080
Why would I know about smugglers?
我怎么会知道走私犯？

556
00:42:00,840 --> 00:42:03,840
- Aren't you a smuggler? - What are you talking about? No.
-你不走私吗？-你在说什么？当然不是

557
00:42:06,000 --> 00:42:08,160
I'm actually really calm by nature.
我天生真的很镇定

558
00:42:08,240 --> 00:42:10,080
I don't like getting mad.
我不喜欢生气

559
00:42:10,160 --> 00:42:13,480
But I'm in a real hurry. Would you like to see me get mad in a hurry?
但是我真的很着急，你想看到我着急的样子吗？

560
00:42:14,040 --> 00:42:15,240
What if you did?
如果我想呢？

561
00:42:16,640 --> 00:42:17,760
What would I do...
我该怎么做……

562
00:42:19,960 --> 00:42:23,880
I might start with making you eat the shells, for a start.
我可能首先要让你个子弹

563
00:42:27,840 --> 00:42:30,040
Do you have the license plate down? Alright.
车牌记下来了吗

564
00:42:30,120 --> 00:42:32,400
Announce it over the radio.
通过广播宣布

565
00:42:32,480 --> 00:42:35,240
The white minivan will be leaving Tophane in two hours.
白色小型货车将在两个小时内离开托普哈内

566
00:42:35,320 --> 00:42:38,600
It's carrying illegal aliens and the fugitive Hamza Kaymak.
它携带着非法移民和在逃的哈姆萨·凯马克

567
00:42:39,400 --> 00:42:41,920
I'm sending you all the info. I'm on my way.
我现在把细节发给你  我正在路上

568
00:42:44,360 --> 00:42:46,080
Nevra...
内芙拉

569
00:42:46,160 --> 00:42:49,440
Did you just point a gun at a man for throwing nuts on the ground?
你是不是刚刚因为一个人把坚果壳扔在地上就用枪指着他？

570
00:42:51,400 --> 00:42:53,640
I can do you one better.
我可以做得更好

571
00:42:54,440 --> 00:42:56,920
I saw a bull in my dream the other day.
前几天我梦见公牛

572
00:42:57,000 --> 00:42:59,560
I pointed my gun at that poor creature.
我用枪指着那头可怜的牛

573
00:43:01,400 --> 00:43:02,640
Um...
嗯……

574
00:43:03,920 --> 00:43:06,560
I should head to the paper.
我要去报社了

575
00:43:08,200 --> 00:43:11,200
I'll clean up my office a bit.
去收拾一下我的办公室

576
00:43:13,240 --> 00:43:14,680
Thank you.
谢谢

577
00:43:16,240 --> 00:43:17,840
I hope you find what you're looking for.
我希望你能找到想要的东西

578
00:43:19,520 --> 00:43:20,600
I already have.
已经找到了

579
00:43:35,360 --> 00:43:39,000
- What happened next? - Next, nothing...
-接下来发生了什么？-接下来什么都没发生

580
00:43:39,080 --> 00:43:42,320
He pointed his gun at me.
他用枪指着我

581
00:43:43,600 --> 00:43:46,840
He took a good look at me, and lowered his gun.
他看着我，放下了枪

582
00:43:48,000 --> 00:43:49,840
I shut the door, of course.
当然  我关上了门

583
00:43:50,480 --> 00:43:52,600
When we went looking for him, he was gone.
当我们去寻找他时，他走了

584
00:43:52,680 --> 00:43:56,120
- You didn't call the cops? - Of course we did. Of course!
-你没给警察打电话吗？-当然报警了！

585
00:43:57,640 --> 00:43:58,880
You must've been so scared.
你一定很害怕

586
00:43:58,960 --> 00:44:02,920
It was really scary in the moment.
当时真的很恐怖

587
00:44:03,000 --> 00:44:05,280
But thinking about it now...
但是现在回想一下

588
00:44:05,960 --> 00:44:08,960
There was this moment when he took a good look at me...
在那一刻，他看着我的时候……

589
00:44:09,520 --> 00:44:12,720
It went on for a few seconds. I felt something...
持续了几秒钟  我感觉到了一些东西……

590
00:44:13,720 --> 00:44:16,640
- I felt something really strange. - What did you feel?
-我觉得有些奇怪-你感觉到了什么？

591
00:44:16,720 --> 00:44:19,040
I mean... It was almost like...
我的意思是……有点像……

592
00:44:19,680 --> 00:44:23,160
Like I was sure he'd never hurt me.
像是我确定他永远都不会伤害我

593
00:44:24,000 --> 00:44:25,600
It was so strange.
好奇怪

594
00:44:25,680 --> 00:44:28,080
Yes. It really is.
是的，确实是

595
00:44:28,160 --> 00:44:31,800
I mean, my whole life,
我是说，我的一生

596
00:44:31,880 --> 00:44:34,880
I've never been so sure that someone wasn't going to hurt me.
我从未如此确定某人不会伤害我

597
00:44:34,960 --> 00:44:37,200
Do you get what I'm saying? Never!
你明白我的意思吗？

598
00:44:37,280 --> 00:44:40,800
No matter whom! Except for you, of course.
不管是谁，除了你，当然

599
00:44:40,880 --> 00:44:44,440
But look... Look, this is burned onto my mind.
但是，你看，这件事已经深深印在了我的脑海中

600
00:44:44,960 --> 00:44:48,120
I'm really little. Eight years old. Maybe nine.
我当时真的很小  八岁也许九岁

601
00:44:49,120 --> 00:44:50,240
We're going on vacation.
我们要去度假

602
00:44:50,320 --> 00:44:54,400
My dad told me he'd teach me how to jump from the pier.
爸爸告诉我，他会教我如何从码头上跳下来

603
00:44:55,000 --> 00:44:56,520
I'm on the pier.
我在码头上

604
00:44:56,600 --> 00:45:00,480
My dad's in the water. He's gesturing me, telling me to jump.
我爸爸在水中他在打手势我，告诉我跳

605
00:45:01,080 --> 00:45:04,640
"Come on, jump." But I can't jump. I couldn't do it.
“来吧，跳吧”  但是我不敢跳，我做不到

606
00:45:05,400 --> 00:45:09,520
I felt my father wouldn't be able to protect me.
我觉得我父亲无法保护我

607
00:45:09,600 --> 00:45:12,680
Do you get what I'm saying? It felt as though...
你明白我的意思吗？就好像……

608
00:45:12,760 --> 00:45:15,560
As though he could hurt me, albeit unintentionally.
好像他会伤害我，尽管是无意的

609
00:45:15,640 --> 00:45:19,720
As though if I were to drown, he wouldn't be able to rescue me.
好像我要淹死了，他也无法解救我

610
00:45:19,800 --> 00:45:22,760
If something were to happen to me, he wouldn't...
如果我发生什么事，他不会……

611
00:45:22,840 --> 00:45:24,560
I couldn't trust my father!
我不能相信我的父亲！

612
00:45:24,640 --> 00:45:26,920
I couldn't trust my father on that day!
那天我不能相信我的父亲！

613
00:45:27,000 --> 00:45:30,120
But whatever it was that was inside that cat...
但是那只猫里面的东西

614
00:45:30,880 --> 00:45:34,200
I trusted that thing, Deva!
我相信他  德瓦！

615
00:45:34,760 --> 00:45:37,200
Could he be someone you know, mom?
妈妈，他有可能是你认识的人吗？

616
00:45:37,280 --> 00:45:41,440
- Or might he know you? - Don't be silly.
-也许他认识你？-说什么傻话

617
00:45:42,000 --> 00:45:44,080
- I wish you did. - Where's your grandfather?
-我希望你认识他  -你祖父在哪里？

618
00:45:44,160 --> 00:45:46,240
- Huh? - I asked you where your grandfather is.
-嗯？-我问你你祖父在哪里

619
00:45:46,800 --> 00:45:49,040
He might be with his girlfriend. I don't know.
他可能和他的女朋友在一起  我不知道

620
00:45:49,120 --> 00:45:50,680
Oh, Deva...
天啊  德瓦……

621
00:46:26,560 --> 00:46:27,720
Hello!
你好！

622
00:46:29,120 --> 00:46:31,560
- Is there anybody there? - I'll be right there.
-有人吗？-我马上来

623
00:46:35,240 --> 00:46:37,960
Hello. How can I help you?
你好，请问什么事？

624
00:46:38,040 --> 00:46:39,400
I was looking for...
我正寻找……

625
00:46:39,480 --> 00:46:43,680
I don't know, a small houseplant.
我不知道，小小的室内植物

626
00:46:46,360 --> 00:46:47,360
Agah?
阿加？

627
00:46:48,960 --> 00:46:51,920
- Agah Beyoglu? - Yes?
-阿加·贝尤鲁？-嗯？

628
00:46:54,160 --> 00:46:56,280
Forgive me, I'm not sure I remember you.
原谅我，我不确定我是否记得你

629
00:46:56,360 --> 00:47:00,400
It's Tayfun, Cemil's friend! From Kambura!
我是塞米尔的朋友  我叫泰丰  来自坎布拉！

630
00:47:03,400 --> 00:47:04,400
Tay...
泰……

631
00:47:05,800 --> 00:47:10,440
Tayfun! Is that you? No way!
泰丰！是你吗？

632
00:47:14,440 --> 00:47:18,000
- What a coincidence! - You haven't changed one bit.
-真是巧合！-你一点都没变

633
00:47:18,080 --> 00:47:23,800
- You're still as handsome as ever. - Stop it. I'm an old man now.
-你仍然像以前一样英俊  -别说了，我现在是个老人

634
00:47:23,880 --> 00:47:25,920
How are you doing? What are you doing here?
你最近好吗？你在这里做什么？

635
00:47:26,000 --> 00:47:31,280
Not much. I own this whole area. I cultivate all kinds of plants.
还行  这块地是我的，我在这里种各种各样的植物

636
00:47:31,360 --> 00:47:33,680
How nice. How...
真好……

637
00:47:33,760 --> 00:47:36,160
I was passing by and I needed some plants for the house.
我路过这里，需要一些室内植物

638
00:47:36,240 --> 00:47:39,000
When I saw this place, I decided to stop by.
当我看到这个地方时，我决定来看看

639
00:47:39,080 --> 00:47:42,400
- What a coincidence. - Don't worry, I've got you.
-太巧了  -别担心，我来帮你

640
00:47:42,480 --> 00:47:45,000
You used to take such good care of us.
你以前很照顾我们

641
00:47:45,080 --> 00:47:48,280
Do you remember all those meals you bought for Cemil and I?
你还记得你为我和塞米尔买的那些饭吗？

642
00:47:48,360 --> 00:47:51,200
We were dirt-poor students back then.
那时我们是贫民窟的学生

643
00:47:52,160 --> 00:47:54,520
Come on. Take a seat. Make yourself at home.
快坐吧  像在自己家一样

644
00:47:54,600 --> 00:47:57,000
You must be busy. I wouldn't want to impose.
你一定很忙  我不想耽误你时间

645
00:47:57,080 --> 00:47:59,880
Don't be ridiculous. I've sent the guys home.
别说笑了  我已经把他们送回家了

646
00:47:59,960 --> 00:48:03,320
It's almost closing time. Come on. Let's catch up.
快到关门的时间了  来吧   我们好好聊聊

647
00:48:03,400 --> 00:48:05,360
- Come on. - OK, then.
-来-好吧

648
00:48:05,440 --> 00:48:10,720
What a coincidence. It's a small world, I'm telling you.
真是巧合  世界真小啊

649
00:48:12,200 --> 00:48:15,600
We have the vehicle in our sights. It's headed right to here.
我们看到那辆车了  它直接开来这里

650
00:48:16,160 --> 00:48:18,240
Alright. Finish the paperwork first.
好，先完成文书工作

651
00:48:18,320 --> 00:48:20,680
Don't let them suspect anything. He might be armed.
不要让他们起疑心  他可能有武器

652
00:48:20,760 --> 00:48:21,840
Of course.
当然

653
00:48:23,280 --> 00:48:26,640
Follow the vehicle, but keep your distance.
跟随车辆，但要保持距离

654
00:48:47,360 --> 00:48:51,320
- Thank you. You're so kind. - Of course.
-谢谢你这么好  -当然

655
00:48:51,400 --> 00:48:54,560
So? Do you and Cemil still see each other?
那你和塞米尔经常见面吗？

656
00:48:55,120 --> 00:48:58,680
Cemil's too busy. He's become an important man.
塞米尔太忙了  他是个重要人物

657
00:48:58,760 --> 00:48:59,960
He stops by now and again.
他偶尔过来看看

658
00:49:00,600 --> 00:49:03,320
- Would you mind if I had some raki? - Of course.
-你介意我喝点红酒吗？-当然不

659
00:49:03,400 --> 00:49:05,600
- It goes down well at this time of day. - Of course.
-每天的这个时候喝点酒最好了  -当然

660
00:49:05,680 --> 00:49:08,200
- Helps me clear my head. - Enjoy yourself.
-帮我清理头脑  -尽情享受

661
00:49:08,280 --> 00:49:10,720
- You prefer coffee, right? - Yes. Thank you.
-你喜欢喝咖啡吧？-是的  谢谢你

662
00:49:10,800 --> 00:49:13,000
You could join me, though. Would you like a glass?
你要喝一杯吗？

663
00:49:13,080 --> 00:49:14,720
No. I shouldn't.
不，我不喝

664
00:49:14,800 --> 00:49:19,880
The other day, I was visiting a friend...
前几天，我去拜访一位朋友……

665
00:49:20,920 --> 00:49:23,840
He set a beautiful table and brought out a bottle of raki.
他摆好桌子，拿出一瓶红酒

666
00:49:23,920 --> 00:49:27,640
We were having so much fun, but after a while, I started feeling really bad.
我们玩得很开心，但是过了一会儿，我开始感到非常难过

667
00:49:27,720 --> 00:49:31,080
- Why? Was it your stomach? - No. Memory loss.
-为什么？肚子不舒服吗？-不是的  我的记忆力减退

668
00:49:31,600 --> 00:49:33,520
I forgot what I came there to do.
我忘了去那儿做什么

669
00:49:33,600 --> 00:49:37,440
I don't have the constitution anymore. You enjoy yourself, I'm fine.
我体格不行了，你喝吧，不用管我

670
00:49:37,520 --> 00:49:39,040
Thank you.
谢谢

671
00:49:48,280 --> 00:49:49,920
Pull over.
靠边停

672
00:49:56,640 --> 00:49:59,000
Good evening. Papers, please.
晚上好，请给我证件

673
00:49:59,080 --> 00:50:00,920
Good evening, officer.
晚上好，长官

674
00:50:02,360 --> 00:50:03,360
Here.
给你

675
00:50:09,400 --> 00:50:11,200
All my papers are there.
我所有的证件都在那里

676
00:50:11,920 --> 00:50:13,200
Everything should be in order.
应该都是井然有序

677
00:50:13,960 --> 00:50:18,400
- I have somewhere to be. - Hold up. I haven't checked yet.
-我有地方要去  -等等，我还没检查

678
00:50:20,000 --> 00:50:23,240
Get out! Out! Out!
下车！下车！下车！

679
00:50:23,320 --> 00:50:25,840
Get out! Get out of the car!
下车！下车！

680
00:50:25,920 --> 00:50:29,920
Get out! Out! Out, I said!
下车！下车！下车！

681
00:50:30,440 --> 00:50:31,760
Get out!
下车！

682
00:50:36,960 --> 00:50:38,520
Put your hands up!
举起手来！

683
00:50:39,280 --> 00:50:41,400
Let me see your hands. Get up! Get up!
把手都举起来，举起来！

684
00:50:50,000 --> 00:50:51,080
Listen up.
听着

685
00:50:53,000 --> 00:50:54,440
They have Hamza.
他们抓住了哈姆萨

686
00:50:55,280 --> 00:50:58,880
- So? What am I supposed to say? - What are you supposed to say?
-那我应该说什么？-你应该说什么？

687
00:51:00,480 --> 00:51:02,520
Hamza will tell them everything he knows.
哈姆萨会告诉他们他所知道的一切

688
00:51:03,360 --> 00:51:04,840
They've forced our hand.
他们逼我们就手

689
00:51:06,400 --> 00:51:08,920
You're going to tell them everything you know, as well, Vural.
你还将告诉他们所有你知道的事情，乌拉尔

690
00:51:09,480 --> 00:51:11,800
Keeping Ufuk in mind, of course.
时刻记住乌福克

691
00:51:12,360 --> 00:51:13,800
Is that clear?
明白了吗？

692
00:51:14,680 --> 00:51:15,760
Of course.
当然

693
00:51:23,760 --> 00:51:26,240
- How many left? - This is the last one.
-还剩几个？-这是最后一个

694
00:51:26,960 --> 00:51:28,920
- Name? - Vural Yasl?.
-名字？-乌拉尔·亚斯莱

695
00:51:32,640 --> 00:51:33,640
Go on.
继续

696
00:51:35,160 --> 00:51:37,000
Take a seat, Vural.
坐吧  乌拉尔

697
00:51:37,600 --> 00:51:41,360
Vural Yasl?... Yes.
乌拉尔·亚斯莱……

698
00:51:42,920 --> 00:51:45,160
Go on. Tell me what happened in Kambura.
告诉我坎布拉发生了什么

699
00:51:46,880 --> 00:51:49,880
How did you escape from prison? Who helped you?
你是如何越狱的？谁帮助了你？

700
00:51:53,200 --> 00:51:54,320
Storks.
鹳

701
00:51:55,320 --> 00:51:56,960
Storks flew me away.
鹳带我飞走了

702
00:51:57,640 --> 00:51:59,520
Then flew me back.
然后又飞了回来

703
00:52:01,440 --> 00:52:03,720
Who would help a poor man such as I?
谁能帮助像我这样的穷人？

704
00:52:03,800 --> 00:52:05,880
I escaped on my own, of course.
我当然是自己逃出来的

705
00:52:05,960 --> 00:52:08,320
Got myself hospitalized, and escaped from there.
让自己进医院，从那里逃了出来

706
00:52:08,920 --> 00:52:12,000
Your brother Tayyar and his family died in a fire in Kambura.
你的兄弟塔亚尔和他的家人在坎布拉死于火灾

707
00:52:12,080 --> 00:52:13,200
What do you know about that?
你对此有什么了解？

708
00:52:13,280 --> 00:52:15,480
I don't know much about it.
我对此不太了解

709
00:52:15,560 --> 00:52:17,720
My brother liked to drink.
我哥哥喜欢喝酒

710
00:52:17,800 --> 00:52:21,120
He was a drunk. He drank like a sponge.
他是个酒鬼  他像海绵吸水一样喝酒

711
00:52:21,200 --> 00:52:25,000
But you can't really help it. You need workers to till the fields.
但真的没办法  需要人来耕地

712
00:52:25,800 --> 00:52:29,320
He came to Kambura every year. Found a job to do one way or another.
他每年都来坎布拉 做各种各样的工作

713
00:52:30,000 --> 00:52:32,440
They worked, him and his whole family.
他和他的家人一起工作

714
00:52:32,520 --> 00:52:35,440
A fire broke out at their house.
他们的房子着火了

715
00:52:35,520 --> 00:52:38,000
His family died in that fire, including all his children.
他的家人在那场大火中丧生，包括他所有的孩子

716
00:52:38,560 --> 00:52:41,320
That drove me up the walls. I headed to Kambura.
那件事使我抓狂了  我去了坎布拉

717
00:52:41,400 --> 00:52:42,840
I asked them what happened.
我问他们发生了什么事

718
00:52:42,920 --> 00:52:45,440
They told me there was a fire, started from a cigarette butt.
他们告诉我起了火，是烟头引发的火灾

719
00:52:46,840 --> 00:52:51,920
I asked the fire brigade and the police. They all told me the same story.
我也问了消防员和警察  他们说法都一样

720
00:52:52,000 --> 00:52:56,520
There was this guy, Halis. He used to run the fire brigade. He's dead now.
当时有一个叫做哈里斯的人  他曾经在消防队，但他现在已经死了

721
00:52:56,600 --> 00:52:59,920
He told us it was a cigarette butt that started the fire.
他告诉我们，那是一支烟蒂引发的火灾

722
00:53:00,680 --> 00:53:02,680
That's what we all knew.
那就是我们知道的一切了

723
00:53:03,400 --> 00:53:05,800
It didn't sit right with me...
在我看来有些不对……

724
00:53:07,120 --> 00:53:11,680
It was a tiny house. I didn't get why they couldn't escape.
那是一间很小的房子  我不知道为什么他们无法逃脱

725
00:53:12,320 --> 00:53:16,600
Then two young men came to talk to me. They were brothers. Twins, apparently.
然后有两个年轻人来跟我说话  他们显然是孪生兄弟

726
00:53:17,480 --> 00:53:21,440
- One was named Seyfi or something. - And the other's name, Umut?
-一个叫塞菲还是什么  -另一个叫乌穆特？

727
00:53:22,320 --> 00:53:24,240
That might've been it. It's been a while.
可能是的，我记不清了

728
00:53:26,880 --> 00:53:29,160
- They're Ufuk's brothers. - Ufuk?
-他们是乌福克的兄弟  -乌福克？

729
00:53:30,000 --> 00:53:32,560
They're actually triplets. Go on with your story.
他们实际上是三胞胎  你继续说

730
00:53:32,640 --> 00:53:36,320
They told me to drop the subject and go home.
他们告诉我放下这件事  回家去

731
00:53:37,000 --> 00:53:40,320
I asked them why. They told me my brother, Tayyar,
我问他们为什么  他们告诉我  我的兄弟塔亚尔，

732
00:53:40,400 --> 00:53:45,840
had raped a young girl from Kambura. And not once, at that. Again and again.
在坎布拉强奸了一个年轻的女孩  而且不止一次

733
00:53:45,920 --> 00:53:48,160
His time must've come, they said.
他们说他该死了

734
00:53:48,960 --> 00:53:51,360
If you keep hanging around, they might decide
如果你还在这里闲逛  他们可能会决定

735
00:53:51,440 --> 00:53:53,920
to take her revenge on you, they said.
为那女孩向你复仇

736
00:53:54,840 --> 00:53:56,720
They weren't talking about someone else.
他们不是在谈论别人

737
00:53:56,800 --> 00:53:59,160
They were threatening me.
他们是在威胁我

738
00:53:59,240 --> 00:54:02,880
"Since you're Tayyar's brother, you might die before your time."
“由于你是塔亚尔的兄弟，你可能会死得很早”

739
00:54:03,440 --> 00:54:07,200
"They'll plug you full of holes." That's exactly what they said.
他们原话说的是“他们会塞满你的洞”

740
00:54:07,280 --> 00:54:11,080
Nevra came to Kambura. We spoke in front of the house, in fact.
内芙拉来到坎布拉  我们曾在门口说话

741
00:54:11,640 --> 00:54:14,040
That's where we ran into each other after all those years.
过了这么多年  我们在那里碰到了

742
00:54:14,600 --> 00:54:16,760
It can't have been more than a week.
就在一周之前

743
00:54:16,840 --> 00:54:18,360
Ufuk found out about it.
乌夫克知道了

744
00:54:19,280 --> 00:54:25,280
Came to me, told me a cop from Istanbul was there to take him away.
来找我，告诉我一个来自伊斯坦布尔的警察在那里要带他走

745
00:54:25,360 --> 00:54:28,000
I asked him what he'd done.
我问他他做了什么

746
00:54:28,720 --> 00:54:30,040
Asked him why...
问他为什么

747
00:54:31,720 --> 00:54:34,720
"I burned that house down," he said. "I killed those people."
他说：“我把那所房子烧毁了  我杀了那些人  ”

748
00:54:35,280 --> 00:54:38,520
But he'd been singing the same refrain for years,
但是他多年来一直在讲同样的故事

749
00:54:39,240 --> 00:54:41,040
so I didn't take him very seriously.
所以我没有当回事

750
00:54:42,920 --> 00:54:44,960
He told me about a girl then.
他曾经跟我提起过一个女孩

751
00:54:45,440 --> 00:54:48,520
There was apparently someone Ufuk had been pining after.
很显然是乌福克喜欢的人

752
00:54:49,520 --> 00:54:52,200
That bastard named Tayyar raped her.
那个叫塔亚尔的混蛋强奸了她

753
00:54:53,920 --> 00:54:56,760
Ufuk decided to kill him in a fire.
乌福克决定在大火中杀死他

754
00:54:57,840 --> 00:54:59,120
That was the night.
那天晚上

755
00:55:00,400 --> 00:55:04,400
He went to the house and put chains around the exits.
他去了房子，用铁链锁住了门窗

756
00:55:05,040 --> 00:55:07,560
Then he started the fire.
然后他放了火

757
00:55:08,680 --> 00:55:10,440
I was stunned, of course.
我当然被惊呆了

758
00:55:10,520 --> 00:55:12,920
Who is this girl?
这个女孩是谁？

759
00:55:13,000 --> 00:55:15,280
Whom did Tayyar rape?
塔亚尔强奸了谁？

760
00:55:15,840 --> 00:55:18,040
Why didn't we ever find out about it?
为什么我们都不知道这件事？

761
00:55:19,040 --> 00:55:21,720
He didn't answer any of it. Just up and left.
他也从没提到过

762
00:55:22,240 --> 00:55:27,240
I thought he was hallucinating again. He'd never been all there, you know.
我以为他又在幻想  他从来没有去过那里

763
00:55:28,080 --> 00:55:31,960
But it all turned out to be true. He really did burn that house down.
但是事实证明  他确实把那所房子烧毁了

764
00:55:33,360 --> 00:55:35,040
Why else would he hang himself?
他为什么还要吊死自己？

765
00:55:35,120 --> 00:55:38,440
Tayyar's family had been inside. His children, his wife.
塔亚尔的妻子、孩子一直在都在房子里

766
00:55:38,520 --> 00:55:39,560
All dead.
全部死了

767
00:55:40,120 --> 00:55:42,520
Who could live with that knowledge?
谁可以忍受这些事？

768
00:55:42,600 --> 00:55:45,400
We saw the flames and ran over.
我们看到了火焰，跑了过去

769
00:55:45,960 --> 00:55:47,400
We gathered around the house...
我们聚集在房子周围

770
00:55:48,080 --> 00:55:50,080
But there was nothing we could do.
但是我们无能为力

771
00:55:50,160 --> 00:55:54,320
Remember that fireman who told us it was a cigarette butt?
还记得那个消防员告诉我们那是烟头吗？

772
00:55:54,400 --> 00:55:56,080
The late Halis?
已故的哈利斯？

773
00:55:56,800 --> 00:55:59,000
He had been protecting Ufuk.
他一直在保护乌福克

774
00:56:00,360 --> 00:56:02,240
He must've known what really happened.
他一定知道真正发生了什么

775
00:56:02,320 --> 00:56:05,360
His brothers must've known also.
他的兄弟们一定也知道

776
00:56:06,160 --> 00:56:09,360
Seyfi and Umut were their names. May God forgive their sins.
塞菲和乌穆特   愿上帝宽恕他们的罪过

777
00:56:09,840 --> 00:56:13,160
Do you think your brother might've really done it?
你认为你的兄弟真的有做吗？

778
00:56:13,240 --> 00:56:16,600
- Could he really have raped that girl? - I don't know.
-他真的强奸了那个女孩吗？-我不知道

779
00:56:17,560 --> 00:56:20,600
He would never do something like that when sober. That, I'm certain of.
清醒的时候，他绝对不会做那样的事情，我敢肯定

780
00:56:20,680 --> 00:56:25,440
But drink? Drink turns people inside out.
但是喝了酒我就不好说了

781
00:56:26,000 --> 00:56:29,920
You never know who people really are. Not even your own brother.
你永远也不知道别人的真面目  即使是你的兄弟

782
00:56:31,200 --> 00:56:33,520
That's why I left Kambura.
这就是为什么我离开了坎布拉

783
00:56:34,080 --> 00:56:35,920
Did they tell you who the girl was?
他们有没有告诉你那个女孩是谁？

784
00:56:36,520 --> 00:56:39,400
- No, they didn't. - Are you sure?
-不，他们没有-你确定吗？

785
00:56:40,480 --> 00:56:42,000
I don't know!
我不知道！

786
00:56:42,080 --> 00:56:44,080
No. I don't know who she was.
不，我不知道她是谁

787
00:56:44,160 --> 00:56:45,800
She must've been really scared.
她一定很害怕

788
00:56:46,400 --> 00:56:48,480
She didn't make herself known.
她没有让别人知道

789
00:56:48,560 --> 00:56:53,320
Let me tell you something. If we'd known about what he did,
这么说吧  如果我们知道他的所作所为

790
00:56:54,360 --> 00:56:56,400
we would've been the ones to burn that house down.
我们才是要烧房子的人

791
00:56:56,480 --> 00:56:59,560
We would've fucked his whole family.
我们会他妈的干翻他们全家人

792
00:57:01,200 --> 00:57:05,520
I mean, when I say fuck... As a figure of speech, you understand.
我的意思是……当我说他妈的时  那只是一种说法  你懂的

793
00:57:05,600 --> 00:57:09,120
We would never touch his wife and his kids.
我们永远不会碰他的妻子和他的孩子

794
00:57:09,200 --> 00:57:12,240
- There's a proper way of doing things. - A proper way...
-做事要有正确的方式  -正确的方式……

795
00:57:13,120 --> 00:57:14,520
You'd fuck him properly.
要好好收拾他

796
00:57:16,000 --> 00:57:19,560
Back then, of course, villages didn't look like they do today.
那时的村庄看起来不像今天

797
00:57:19,640 --> 00:57:20,640
They were properly rural.
他们是农村人

798
00:57:21,360 --> 00:57:23,440
I was in some county in Anatolia,
我在安纳托利亚的某个县，

799
00:57:23,520 --> 00:57:27,440
working as a court clerk.
担任法院书记员

800
00:57:28,120 --> 00:57:30,160
I come across this murder file.
我碰到了这个谋杀案

801
00:57:30,240 --> 00:57:32,640
I open it up and look at the suspect's statement.
我看着它，看看犯罪嫌疑人的陈述

802
00:57:32,720 --> 00:57:35,680
He's a young man. 18 or so.
他是18岁左右的年轻人

803
00:57:36,240 --> 00:57:38,040
His father takes him aside,
父亲把他带到旁边

804
00:57:38,120 --> 00:57:42,440
tells him about the blood feud his family's in.
告诉他家族的世仇

805
00:57:42,520 --> 00:57:47,120
They looked into it after the fact. It had been going for 60-70 years.
事后他们调查了这件事  仇恨已经存在了六七十年

806
00:57:47,200 --> 00:57:51,640
Two families, killing each other one by one.
两个家族  互相残杀

807
00:57:52,320 --> 00:57:56,760
Anyway, the father says to his son, "It's our turn to take a life."
总之  男孩的父亲告诉他  “轮到我们杀人了”

808
00:57:56,840 --> 00:58:00,320
"You're going to do it. You're young, you won't do much time."
“你去做  你还年轻  不用做很久的牢”

809
00:58:01,240 --> 00:58:04,840
The boy's father brings out the gun. It's a family heirloom.
男孩的父亲拿给他一把枪  是家族的传家宝

810
00:58:05,360 --> 00:58:09,360
They've been using that same gun to kill their enemies for 70 years.
他们用同一把枪杀掉敌人，用了七十年

811
00:58:09,440 --> 00:58:11,560
Right there, the father teaches him how to use it.
那时  父亲教他怎么用枪

812
00:58:11,640 --> 00:58:15,480
"Here's how you load the chamber. Here's how you cock the gun."
“要这样装子弹，这样开枪”

813
00:58:15,560 --> 00:58:19,040
"You got it?" his father asks the boy. "I got it," the boy says.
父亲问他“你学会了吗？”男孩说“学会了”

814
00:58:19,120 --> 00:58:23,240
He takes the gun in his hand, and shoots his father. Just like that.
他手里拿着枪，向父亲射击

815
00:58:24,000 --> 00:58:25,760
Doesn't even hesitate.
毫不犹豫

816
00:58:25,840 --> 00:58:28,320
The gendarme asks him, "Why did you do it?"
宪兵问他：“你为什么这样做？”

817
00:58:28,400 --> 00:58:32,040
"Why else?" says the boy. "I wanted to end the feud."
“为什么呢？”男孩说：“我想结束仇恨”

818
00:58:32,120 --> 00:58:34,280
They ask the boy again in court.
他们再次在法庭上问男孩

819
00:58:34,360 --> 00:58:39,360
"We get it, you wanted the feud to end. But how could you shoot your father?"
“我们明白了，你想结束世仇，但是你怎么能枪杀你的父亲？”

820
00:58:39,440 --> 00:58:42,960
"Well," the boy says, "I've always hated my father."
男孩说：“好吧，我一直恨我父亲”

821
00:58:43,040 --> 00:58:45,960
"I would've killed him a long time ago, but I didn't have a gun."
“我很久以前就想杀了他，但我没有枪”

822
00:58:50,800 --> 00:58:52,920
- That's some story. - It is.
-那是个好故事-是的

823
00:58:53,000 --> 00:58:55,480
What about the blood feud? Did it end?
世仇后来怎样了？结束了吗？

824
00:58:55,560 --> 00:58:58,040
It did. The other family was baffled.
结束了，另一个家族感到困惑

825
00:58:58,120 --> 00:59:00,360
The feud ended, but it was the boy that suffered for it.
仇恨结束了，但受苦的是男孩

826
00:59:00,960 --> 00:59:04,520
He was sentenced to life. Isn't that how it always goes?
他被判处无期徒刑  不是一直如此吗？

827
00:59:04,600 --> 00:59:06,840
The young are always the ones who end up suffering.
年轻人永远是遭受苦难的人

828
00:59:06,920 --> 00:59:09,680
- It's all over the TV. - Why do you say that?
-电视上总能看到  -为什么这么说？

829
00:59:10,640 --> 00:59:14,160
Why hasn't there ever been an elderly suicide bomber, for example?
例如，为什么从来没有过一个老人用自杀式炸弹袭击？

830
00:59:15,320 --> 00:59:17,400
It's always the young who blow themselves up.
永远都是年轻人把自己炸飞

831
00:59:17,480 --> 00:59:19,480
It's always the young ones. Never the elderly.
永远是年轻人  永远不会是老年人

832
00:59:19,560 --> 00:59:23,800
The young ones die so quick, so easily... It's a real pity.
年轻人死得如此之快，如此之轻易  这真是可惜

833
00:59:24,400 --> 00:59:26,440
Their lives have no value.
他们的命毫无价值

834
